claim.claim-text:
1. A heat sink comprising:
a base;
a heat-transferring member attached to the base;
a plurality of first fins stacked together and attached to the heat-transferring member for dissipating heat; and
a reinforcement fixed on the base and joining at least one of the first fins;
wherein the heat-transferring member is a heat pipe;
wherein the heat pipe has a U-shaped configuration and comprises an evaporating portion fixed on the base and two condensing portions extending perpendicularly from opposite ends of the evaporating portion, away from the base and through the fins; and
wherein the reinforcement and the heat pipe joint the fins at three supporting points, the three supporting points being at three points of a triangle, respectively.

9. A heat sink comprising:
a base;
a heat-transferring member attached to the base;
a plurality of first fins stacked together and attached to the heat-transferring member for dissipating heat; and
a reinforcement fixed on the base and joining at least one of the first fins;
wherein the heat-transferring member is a heat pipe;
wherein the reinforcement is a pole; and
wherein the pole defines at least one groove receiving the at least one of the fins.
